System OverviewThe Artificial Cognition Engine (ACE) is a decoupled, event-driven AI Operating System designed to support aging in place.It is a continuous perception-action loop that maintains an evolving World Model of a user's life.The system optimizes interactions against a hierarchy of human-centric objectives rather than functioning as a reactive chatbot.2. Core Architectural PrinciplesCognition is Independent: Telephony, web apps, and background monitors act merely as sensory inputs, while cognition happens asynchronously on an event bus.Epistemic Humility: The system strictly separates Facts, Beliefs, and Predictions, and never presents an Inference as a Fact.Objective-Driven: Every output evaluates candidate actions against System, User, and Session Objectives.Auditable Reasoning: All Beliefs and Predictions must trace back to verifiable Facts via a Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG).3. Service BoundariesServiceResponsibilityCore Data DependencyVoice IngressWebRTC/Telephony streaming, VAD, STT, TTS.Redis (Sub-10ms Session Context).Cognition Pipeline10-stage asynchronous perception-to-action loop.ACE Event Bus.Memory EngineManages episodic, semantic, procedural, and emotional states.Postgres + pgvector + Graph DB.Planning EngineMulti-objective optimization for next-best-action.Active World Model Cache.Caregiver APISecure, read-only exposure of trajectory trends and facts.Graph DB (Fact nodes only).4. Non-Functional Requirements (Latency Budgets)Voice VAD Threshold is dynamic, defaulting to 1500ms and tuned via Procedural Memory.Conversational time-to-first-audio must not exceed 800ms.Procedural Memory fetch must resolve in < 15ms during call initialization.Asynchronous background loop processing must complete within 45 seconds of a ConversationCompleted event.
